The tragic shooting at Columbine High School left 15 dead, including the gunmen.
Confusion over the death toll arose due to overlapping areas covered by SWAT teams.
Despite the fear and sadness, communities united in support.
Pat Buchanan dismissed stricter gun laws as a solution.
The return to school was delayed to allow students to attend funerals.
The community rallied together, emphasizing the need for unity and love over hate.
Gore urged parents to prioritize their children and make positive changes in the wake of the tragedy.
